title: TEMECULA: Genealogical society to hold open house
text:
STAFF REPORT
Published: Oct. 9, 2015 3:35 p.m. TEMECULA: Genealogical society to hold open house Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Temecula City Hall FIELDING BUCK, , FILE PHOTO Related article » The 10th annual Open House of the Temecula Valley Genealogical Society will be held 6:30 to 8:30 pm. Monday, Oct. 12 in the Community Room at Temecula City Hall, 41000 Main St.
The theme is ‘Bridging the Past to the Future” and with multiple exhibits, will be based on the San Francisco World’s Fair and the California Exposition in San Diego’s Balboa Park, each of which took place a hundred years ago.
Visitors can learn about ways the society can assist them in their genealogical research There will be displays on the society’s DNA group, special interest groups and computer users group, as well as exhibits from the Temecula Historical Society and Temecula Historical Museum.
Information: Barbgma9@yahoo.com
